<subSubSection id="7F906500D126FFCFFFDAAFEC4D05D1E4" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph id="3735368BD126FFCFFFDAAFEC4D05D1E4" blockId="117.[93,620,395,1180]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
DEFINITION: All taxa sharing a more recent common ancestor with 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFE6CAFCE4F95D1E4" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1983" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Melanosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFE6CAFCE4F95D1E4" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Melanosaurus maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than with 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFEE6AFA04D1AD1E7" authorityName="sensu Sullivan" authorityYear="1979" box="[326,588,455,478]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Glyptosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFEE6AFA04D1AD1E7" box="[326,588,455,478]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Glyptosaurus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F906500D126FFCFFFDAAF844FEAD249" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3735368BD126FFCFFFDAAF844FEAD249" blockId="117.[93,620,395,1180]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
DIAGNOSIS: 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFEB6AF834D7BD1C2" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[278,557,484,507]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Melanosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFEB6AF834D7BD1C2" box="[278,557,484,507]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Melanosaurus maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFFFDAC654ED6D221" baseAuthorityName="Meszoely" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[93,384,514,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Arpadosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gazinorum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFFFDAC654ED6D221" box="[93,384,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Arpadosaurus gazinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are united in this analysis based on one unambiguous synapomorphy: 88(1) supratemporal 3 times as long as deep.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F906500D126FFCFFFDAAC114EF7D4A5" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3735368BD126FFCFFFDAAC114EF7D4A5" blockId="117.[93,620,395,1180]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
COMMENTS: 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD126FFCFFEBAAC1F4EF8D2B7" author="Estes, R." box="[282,430,632,654]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" refId="ref87654" refString="Estes, R. 1983. Sauria terrestria, Amphisbaenia. New York: Gustav Fischer Verlag, 249 pp." type="book" year="1983">Estes (1983)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that any re-evaluation of the interrelationships of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFFFDACD54FA1D2F1" baseAuthorityName="Meszoely" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[93,247,690,712]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Arpadosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gazinorum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFFFDACD54FA1D2F1" box="[93,247,690,712]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">A. gazinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFE91ACD44E97D2F1" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[305,449,691,712]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Melanosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFE91ACD44E97D2F1" box="[305,449,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">M. maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must consider the possibility of the synonymy of the two. Indeed, the present analysis finds no diagnostic characters to separate these two taxa. However, the absence of autapomorphies for these taxa may be related to the incompleteness of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFF63AD054E32D34E" baseAuthorityName="Meszoely" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[195,356,866,887]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Arpadosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gazinorum">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFF63AD054E32D34E" box="[195,356,866,887]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">A. gazinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains. If they are considered conspecific specimens, then 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFD86AD194F9DD38B" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="1979" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Melanosaurini">Melanosaurini</taxonomicName>
is taxonomically synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFFFDADDF4E3BD3F6" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[93,365,952,975]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Melanosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFFFDADDF4E3BD3F6" box="[93,365,952,975]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Melanosaurus maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the present topology. However, the current definition of 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFFFDAD934E50D433" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="1979" box="[93,262,1012,1034]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Melanosaurini">Melanosaurini</taxonomicName>
allows for the addition of taxa if future discoveries produce new taxa more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFED7AA484D5FD47D" baseAuthorityName="Estes" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[375,521,1071,1092]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Melanosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximus">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFED7AA484D5FD47D" box="[375,521,1071,1092]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">M. maximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="F08A4D08D126FFCFFFFDAA2C4E09D45B" authorityName="sensu Sullivan" authorityYear="1979" box="[93,351,1099,1122]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Glyptosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="05FEEA99D126FFCFFFFDAA2C4E09D45B" box="[93,351,1099,1122]" italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Glyptosaurus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The current definition also maintains the perceived spirit of usage set forth in 
<bibRefCitation id="531B4B7AD126FFCFFF49AAE14ECAD4A5" author="Sullivan, R. M." box="[233,412,1158,1180]" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref100591" refString="Sullivan, R. M. 1979. Revision of the Paleogene genus Glyptosaurus (Reptilia, Anguidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 163 (1): 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1979">Sullivan (1979)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
